Subject: [PATCH] Phase C-6 L59: return the top interpreted frame to an even PC (A64/C64 sentry)

The JavaCalls call_stub runs in C64 mode (fix #10 sets its entry cap bit0=1
so the C++ indirect call enters C64 cleanly). It reaches the interpreter
entry with `blr x4`; on this Morello, BLR to an even target keeps C64 and
lands on an even PC (so leaving entry_point bit0=0, fix #17b, is correct —
setting bit0=1 lands the PC on an odd address and faults at the entry's
first instruction). BUT the `blr x4` bakes PSTATE.C64 (=1) into the return
sentry's address bit0, and RET sets PC = sentry.address WITHOUT clearing
bit0 — so when the interpreted method finally `ret`s, PC lands on the odd
sentry address (0x...c1) and instruction fetch faults SIGBUS / BUS_ADRALN.

Fix: in TemplateTable::_return, clear bit0 of lr (new MacroAssembler
helper cap_clear_bit0: andr the address with ~1, then SCVALUE it back into
the capability preserving tag/bounds) just before `ret`. This is a no-op
for returns to interpreted callers (their return-entry addresses are
adr-computed and already even); it only matters for the top frame that
returns to the call_stub.

RESULT: the top <clinit> returns to the call_stub at an even PC; runtime
class loading advances from java/lang/RuntimeException all the way to
java/lang/String$CaseInsensitiveComparator (many JavaCalls cycles). Next
fault is in the call_stub's own epilogue return to libjvm (L60).

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>

